# Snake Game Project Rules

## Project Overview
- Language: C (C11 standard)
- Graphics: raylib
- Build: Make (MinGW-w64)
- Platform: Windows

## Architecture (MVC Pattern)
- Model Layer: snake.c, food.c (NO raylib)
- Logic Layer: game.c (NO raylib)
- View Layer: renderer.c (raylib OK)
- Controller: main.c (raylib input OK)

## Naming Conventions
- Functions: snake_case (e.g., snake_move, game_update)
- Types/Structs: PascalCase (e.g., Snake, GameState)
- Constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE (e.g., GRID_WIDTH)
- Global vars: g_ prefix (e.g., g_game_state)
- Static vars: s_ prefix (e.g., s_frame_count)
- Pointers: p_ prefix (e.g., p_snake)

## Code Style
- 4 spaces indentation (no tabs)
- Opening brace on same line
- Max function length: 50 lines
- Max parameters: 4
- Always use braces for if/for/while

## Required Practices
- NULL pointer check at function start
- Free all malloc'd memory
- Use constants instead of magic numbers
- Doxygen comments for public functions

## Prohibited
- raylib in Model/Logic layers
- Global variable abuse
- goto statements
- Magic numbers
- Circular dependencies

## File Structure
- Headers: include/*.h
- Sources: src/*.c
- Tests: test/test_*.c

## Error Handling Pattern
```c
bool function_name(Type* p_param) {
    if (p_param == NULL) {
        fprintf(stderr, "Error: NULL pointer\n");
        return false;
    }
    // ... logic ...
    return true;
}
```

## Comment Style (Doxygen)
```c
/**
 * Brief description.
 * @param p_param Parameter description
 * @return Return value description
 */
```

## Build Commands
- make: Build project
- make clean: Clean build
- make test: Run tests
